headline: Meet the Historically Boring Asset That Has Risen 610% Since 2000 and Crushed the S&P 500 Index
summary: Stocks have always been viewed as the more aggressive investment that carry more risk but generate higher returns compared to safer assets like bonds.  Younger investors are now encouraged to be more aggressive toward stocks earlier in their lives due to longer life expectancies and the higher cost of living.  Several years ago, if you had told many investors that SPDR Gold Shares (NYSEMKT: GLD) would surpass $315 and an ounce of gold would surpass $3,400, they might have laughed.
